        <div class="inner">
          <p class="supertitle">Full Time / Boston, MA</p>
  <h1>QA Engineer  </h1>

  <div class="columns generic ">
    <div class="column main">
      <p>As a Veson Nautical QA Engineer you will help ensure product quality and customer satisfaction for the world’s leading developer of commercial maritime shipping software. You will be responsible for the development and execution of manual and automated test cases and QA processes that ensure quality throughout our release schedule. You will have a deep understanding of our customer’s workflow and processes and uncover and diagnose problems in new and existing code by running customer centric scenarios. You will document tests, test plans and cases. You will have an important role in notifying developers, managers, field personnel of quality issues, and will lead the effort to identify areas for improvement of overall system quality.</p>

<p>Requirements</p>

<ul>
<li>0-4 years formal testing or development experience</li>
<li>Passion for quality</li>
<li>Loves a good puzzle and troubleshooting complex problems</li>
<li>Generally enjoys working with software and computers</li>
<li>Experience in manual testing required</li>
<li>Willingness to conduct ad-hoc or exploratory testing with thin documentation</li>
<li>Experience in automated testing a strong plus</li>
<li>Familiarity with object oriented programming languages (C#, Java, or comparable)</li>
<li>Familiarity with at least one scripting language (VB Script, PHP, Python, Perl, Ruby, etc.)</li>
<li>Familiarity with a defect tracking tool a plus</li>
<li>Relational database knowledge (SQL Server) a plus</li>
<li>Ability to advocate for software changes as necessary</li>
<li>Strong written and oral communication skills</li>
<li>Maritime industry experience a plus</li>
<li>Desire to work in fast-paced, entrepreneurial setting</li>
<li>Proactive, positive approach to work</li>
<li>Legal right to work in U.S.</li>
</ul>


<p>About Veson Nautical www.veson.com</p>

<p>Veson Nautical delivers software solutions and services that enable the commercial maritime community to make moreinformed decisions, simplify everyday operations, and maximize profits. With offices in Boston, Athens, Rotterdam and Singapore, Veson Nautical is a dynamic organization with a committed team of executives, product managers, software developers, and customer service experts. Dedicated to ensuring the highest levels of customer satisfaction, Veson Nautical brings decades of experience, technical knowledge, enthusiasm and commitment to clients around the world. The combination of exceptional market growth and leading market position make this a superb opportunity for the right candidate.</p>

<p>Veson Nautical offers</p>

<ul>
<li>Competitive compensation</li>
<li>Three weeks of vacation to start plus 11 holidays</li>
<li>Generous Health, Dental, Life &amp; Disability Insurance</li>
<li>Flexible Spending Plan + $500 employer contribution</li>
<li>401K + 4% employer match</li>
<li>Health Club membership subsidy</li>
<li>Free Monthly T pass</li>
<li>Free Friday lunches</li>
<li>Friendly, informal work environment</li>
<li>Offices in Boston’s Back Bay</li>
</ul>


<p>To Apply</p>

